{
  "texts": [
    "[17,18] α |0⟩ + β |1⟩ → α |0 c ⟩ + β |1 c ⟩(34)using only CNOT gates and in depth ⌈log 2 (c)⌉.",
    "We will need this subroutine because we often want to perform many CSWAP gates with disjoint targets but controlled by the same register.",
    "We can accomplish this in shallower depth by copying the control register and applying the CSWAPs in parallel.",
    "Clader et al. [20] avoided this issue by assuming the ability to do FANOUT-CNOT with an arbitrary number of targets, which is a Clifford gate, in a single time step.The protocol for copying consists of ⌈log 2 (c)⌉ sequential depth-1 operations, labeled by 0,..., ⌈log 2 (c)⌉-1.",
    "We refer to these as copying layers."
  ]
}